content:
Creating a web page using HTML and styling it with CSS is a great way to get started with web development. Here's a step-by-step guide to help you create a simple web page:

### Step 1: Set Up Your Environment
1. **Text Editor:** Use a text editor like Visual Studio Code, Sublime Text, or even Notepad++.
2. **Browser:** You'll need a web browser (e.g., Chrome, Firefox) to view your web page.

### Step 2: Create Your HTML File
1. **Create a New File:** Open your text editor and create a new file. Save it as `index.html`.

2. **Basic HTML Structure:** Add the following basic HTML structure to your `index.html` file:

   ```html
   <!DOCTYPE html>
   <html lang="en">
   <head>
       <meta charset="UTF-8">
       <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
       <title>My Web Page</title>
       <link rel="stylesheet" href="styles.css">
   </head>
   <body>
       <header>
           <h1>Welcome to My Web Page</h1>
       </header>
       <nav>
           <ul>
               <li><a href="#home">Home</a></li>
               <li><a href="#about">About</a></li>
               <li><a href="#contact">Contact</a></li>
           </ul>
       </nav>
       <main>
           <section id="home">
               <h2>Home</h2>
               <p>This is the home section of the page.</p>
           </section>
           <section id="about">
               <h2>About</h2>
               <p>This section provides information about the page.</p>
           </section>
           <section id="contact">
               <h2>Contact</h2>
               <p>Here is how you can contact us.</p>
           </section>
       </main>
       <footer>
           <p>&copy; 2023 My Web Page</p>
       </footer>
   </body>
   </html>
   ```

### Step 3: Create Your CSS File
1. **Create a New File:** In the same directory, create a new file and save it as `styles.css`.

2. **Add Basic Styles:** Add the following CSS to your `styles.css` file:

   ```css
   body {
       font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
       line-height: 1.6;
       margin: 0;
       padding: 0;
   }

   header {
       background-color: #4CAF50;
       color: white;
       padding: 10px 0;
       text-align: center;
   }

   nav ul {
       background-color: #333;
       list-style: none;
       padding: 0;
       display: flex;
       justify-content: center;
   }

   nav ul li {
       margin: 0 15px;
   }

   nav ul li a {
       color: white;
       text-decoration: none;
   }

   main {
       padding: 20px;
   }

   section {
       margin-bottom: 20px;
   }

   footer {
       background-color: #333;
       color: white;
       text-align: center;
       padding: 10px 0;
       position: fixed;
       width: 100%;
       bottom: 0;
   }
   ```

### Step 4: View Your Web Page
1. **Open `index.html`:** Double-click on the `index.html` file or open it in your web browser to view your web page.

### Step 5: Customize
Feel free to modify the content and styles to better suit your needs. Add more sections, change colors, adjust the layout, and experiment with different CSS properties to enhance your web page.

That's it! You've created a basic web page using HTML and styled it with CSS. You can build on this foundation by learning more about HTML5 elements, CSS3 properties, and responsive design techniques.
